---
import ResourceLayout from '../../components/ResourceLayout.astro';
---

<ResourceLayout
  icon="🩺"
  eyebrow="Healthcare navigation"
  title="Finding Healthcare"
  introduction="Learn where to go when you need healthcare in Canada, including family doctors, walk-in clinics, virtual care, and community health centres."
>
  <section>
    <h2>Family doctors</h2>
    <p>
      A family doctor provides ongoing care, manages long-term health concerns,
      orders tests, and refers patients to specialists when needed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Walk-in clinics</h2>
    <p>
      Walk-in clinics can help with non-emergency medical concerns when your
      family doctor is unavailable or when you do not yet have one.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Virtual care</h2>
    <p>
      Some healthcare concerns can be discussed by telephone or video. Virtual
      care may not be suitable when a physical examination is needed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <aside class="notice">
    <strong>Emergency warning</strong>
    <p>
      Call 911 when someone has severe difficulty breathing, chest pain, signs
      of stroke, loss of consciousness, or another life-threatening emergency.
    </p>
  </aside>
</ResourceLayout>